{"id": "1508228530289508483", "channel_id": "1505262542552043600", "author_id": "259018461458595850", "author_name": "amstelredam", "content": "I’m really heartbroken now… Light announced that he will not react to who cursed him and his family, which I think is a right thing to do, but combined with the fact that my suggestions on texture rarely get responses despite that most of my suggestions have nothing to do with both pricing and game-balancing but mostly focused on texture itself…I feel like I, who can say I’ve and will never curse Light and his family, was unfairly categorized as those who curse… I really really don’t understand. It’s not even like I’m asking for more rewards or benefits from the system, what I want is but to maintain the good story writing style from Arc 1 ch 1~6. Only if Light did mute those who cursed ONLY, his words would be trustworthy and reliable, yet the truth is more like even the developer-gamer dynamic is another overblown lapping session, I playing the player and Light playing the developer who claims to listen to the gamers…", "timestamp": "2026-05-24T22:01:43.152000+00:00", "type": 19, "thread_id": "1505262542552043600", "mentions": ["472371439555575809"], "reactions": [{"emoji": "aigiscookie", "emoji_id": "1448403059431444630", "count": 3}, {"emoji": "😭", "emoji_id": null, "count": 1}, {"emoji": "💯", "emoji_id": null, "count": 1}], "reply_to": "1508167306105192469"}
